<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="546" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,223,790]" pageId="25" pageNumber="546">
COMMENTS: 
<typeStatus box="[331,389,476,502]" pageId="25" pageNumber="546">Type</typeStatus>
locality upper Umlaas River (= Camperdown, 
<collectingRegion box="[925,1112,475,502]" country="South Africa" name="KwaZulu-Natal" pageId="25" pageNumber="546">KwaZulu-Natal</collectingRegion>
) according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Gyldenstolpe, N." pageId="25" pageNumber="546" pagination="1 - 116" refId="ref28755" refString="Gyldenstolpe, N. (1926) Types of birds in the Royal Natural History Museum in Stockholm. Arkiv f or Zoologi, 19, 1 - 116." type="journal article" year="1926">Gyldenstolpe (1926)</bibRefCitation>
. However, Wahlberg stayed at the mouth of the uMlazi River from 
<date box="[1024,1203,511,537]" pageId="25" pageNumber="546" value="1841-03-11">11 March 1841</date>
until at least 7 May (
<bibRefCitation author="Brinck, P." box="[159,312,547,574]" pageId="25" pageNumber="546" refId="ref28132" refString="Brinck, P. (1955) Swedish exploration of South African animal life during 200 years. In: Hanstrom, B., Brinck, P. &amp; Rudebeck, G. (Eds.), South African Animal Life. Vol. 1. Almquist &amp; Wiksell, Stockholm, pp. 11 - 61." type="book" year="1955">Brinck 1955</bibRefCitation>
). Entries in the journal are intermittent through March and there are only two entries for April. The next entry on 7 May states that he had returned to Congella, Durban. There is no note that Wahlberg had gone to Camperdown during this period, and all specimens collected in March, April and early May are labelled uMlazi River or Durban (the latter probably in error). The 
<typeStatus box="[910,961,656,682]" pageId="25" pageNumber="546">type</typeStatus>
locality can be restricted to uMlazi River mouth, near Durban. In his 
<typeStatus box="[479,530,692,718]" pageId="25" pageNumber="546">type</typeStatus>
catalogue, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gyldenstolpe, N." box="[666,955,691,718]" pageId="25" pageNumber="546" pagination="1 - 116" refId="ref28755" refString="Gyldenstolpe, N. (1926) Types of birds in the Royal Natural History Museum in Stockholm. Arkiv f or Zoologi, 19, 1 - 116." type="journal article" year="1926">Gyldenstolpe (1926: 46)</bibRefCitation>
observed that 
<bibRefCitation author="Sundevall, C. J." box="[1125,1387,691,718]" pageId="25" pageNumber="546" pagination="96 - 111" refId="ref29984" refString="Sundevall, C. J. (1850) Foglar fran sodra Afrika. Ofversigt af Kongliga Vetenskaps-akademiens forhandlingar, 7 (4), 96 - 111." type="journal article" year="1850">Sundevall (1850: 103)</bibRefCitation>
had priority over Cabanis’ paper of the same year and thus that 
<taxonomicName authority="Cabanis, 1851" authorityName="Cabanis" authorityYear="1851" box="[819,1200,727,754]" class="Aves" family="Locustellidae" genus="Catriscus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="546" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis box="[819,1030,727,754]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="546">Catriscus apicalis</emphasis>
Cabanis, 1851
</taxonomicName>
(corrected date, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Dickinson, E. C. &amp; Overstreet, L. K. &amp; Dowsett, R. J. &amp; Bruce, M. D." box="[151,403,763,790]" pageId="25" pageNumber="546" refId="ref28440" refString="Dickinson, E. C., Overstreet, L. K., Dowsett, R. J. &amp; Bruce, M. D. (2011) Priority! The Dating of Scientific Names in Ornithology: a Directory to the Literature and its Reviewers. Aves Press, Northampton, 319 pp." type="book" year="2011">Dickinson et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
) is a subjective junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Sundevall, 1850" authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1850" box="[796,1284,763,790]" class="Aves" family="Locustellidae" genus="Bradypterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="25" pageNumber="546" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brevirostris">
<emphasis box="[796,1083,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="546">Bradypterus brevirostris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sundevall, C. J." box="[1091,1284,763,790]" pageId="25" pageNumber="546" pagination="96 - 111" refId="ref29984" refString="Sundevall, C. J. (1850) Foglar fran sodra Afrika. Ofversigt af Kongliga Vetenskaps-akademiens forhandlingar, 7 (4), 96 - 111." type="journal article" year="1850">Sundevall, 1850</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
